'''Michal <U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k''' (born December 31, 1988 in [[Vla<U+0161>im]], [[Czechoslovakia]]) is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] professional [[ice hockey]] [[Winger (ice hockey)|left winger]] who is currently playing for the [[Florida Panthers]] of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL).

He appeared in two [[Memorial Cup]]s in [[2006 Memorial Cup|2006]] and [[2007 Memorial Cup|2007]] with the [[Vancouver Giants]] during his [[major junior hockey|major junior]] career, capturing the championship in 2007 while earning the [[Ed Chynoweth Trophy]] as the tournament's leading scorer.

==Playing career==
After being selected 25th overall by the [[Vancouver Giants]] in the 2005 [[Canadian Hockey League|CHL]] Import Draft, <U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k debuted with Vancouver in [[2005<U+2013>06 WHL season|2005<U+2013>06]] and appeared in the [[2006 Memorial Cup]] as the Giants captured the [[Ed Chynoweth Trophy|WHL title]].  Although the Giants were eliminated in the semi-finals, they were chosen to host the next year's [[2007 Memorial Cup]]. After scoring 55 points in 56 games, <U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k led the [[Western Hockey League|WHL]] in playoff scoring with 26 points in 22 games, then earned the [[Ed Chynoweth Trophy]] as the Memorial Cup's leading scorer en route to the [[2007 Memorial Cup|2007 CHL title]].

[[Image:Tyson Sexsmith & Michal Repik.jpg|thumb|left|Repik with [[Vancouver Giants|Giants]] teammate [[Tyson Sexsmith]].]]
In the subsequent [[2007 NHL Entry Draft]], he was drafted in the 2nd round, 40th overall, by the [[Florida Panthers]].  At mid-season, he had been ranked 46th among draft-eligible skaters playing in North America by Central Scouting Services.<ref>{{cite web|title=NHL Central Scouting Service Mid Term Rankings - January 2007|url=http://cdn.nhl.com/futures/cssrankings/na_skater0107.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=2008-11-15|publisher=[[National Hockey League]]}}</ref> Upon being drafted, <U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k returned to the WHL for a third and final season with Vancouver and scored a junior career high 61 points.  He was limited to just 51 games after suffering a [[concussion]] on a hit from [[Everett Silvertips]] [[defenceman (ice hockey)|defenceman]] [[Dane Crowley]] on December 1, 2007 (the injury has affected <U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k's sense of smell up to his rookie season in the [[American Hockey League|AHL]]).<ref name=coaster>{{Cite web|title=Repik riding pro hockey roller-coaster|url=http://www.canada.com/theprovince/news/sports/story.html?id=bfcb8a7d-9f7b-4629-9869-ecab05af09e2|accessdate=2008-12-15|date=2008-12-13|publisher=''[[The Province]]''}}</ref>  Defending their Memorial Cup title, the Giants were eliminated in the second round of the WHL playoffs by eventual [[2008 Memorial Cup]] champions, the [[Spokane Chiefs]].

<U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k was assigned by the Panthers to the [[Rochester Americans]] of the American Hockey League (AHL) for his first professional season in [[2008<U+2013>09 AHL season|2008<U+2013>09]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Amerks get six more from Florida|url=http://www.oursportscentral.com/services/releases/?id=3722899|accessdate=2008-09-30|date=2008-09-29}}</ref>  Called up from Rochester in December, he scored his first NHL goal in his NHL debut on December 8, 2008, in a 4<U+2013>3 [[overtime (hockey)|overtime]] victory over the [[Ottawa Senators]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Weiss' OT goal gave Panthers win over Senators|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5gysKr8DzM3-bgmha-l6ZuCinKd8wD94V362O0|accessdate=2008-12-15|date=2008-12-08|publisher=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>  He played in 5 games total for the Panthers during the season, taylling 2 goals.  With the Americans, he tallied 49 points in 75 games. for 2010-2011 he is back to Rochester and has started the season with a bang recording 21 points in 15 games.

==International play==
<U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k competed for the Czech Republic's under-20 team at the [[2007 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2007 World Junior Championships]] in [[Sweden]].  He failed to register a point in six games as the Czechs were eliminated in the quarter-finals by Sweden.  Poised to make a second appearance at the [[World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|World Junior Championships]] in [[2008 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2008]] in his home country, <U+0158>ep<U+00ED>k was unable to participate due to a [[concussion]] suffered in the month preceding the tournament.<ref name=coaster/>

==Awards==
*Won the [[Ed Chynoweth Cup|President's Cup]] ([[Western Hockey League|WHL]] champions) with the [[Vancouver Giants]] in [[2005<U+2013>06 WHL season|2006]].
*[[Western Hockey League|WHL]] playoff leading scorer in [[2006<U+2013>07 WHL season|2007]].
*Won the [[Memorial Cup]] ([[Canadian Hockey League|CHL]] champions) with the Vancouver Giants in [[2007 Memorial Cup|2007]].
*Won the [[Ed Chynoweth Trophy]] ([[Memorial Cup]] leading scorer) in 2007.
*Named to the [[Memorial Cup]] All-Star Team in 2007.

